5000|$|The court {{establishes}} that a test, {{proposed by}} John Henry Wigmore, might {{be employed to}} determine whether a specific communication is privileged or not. The [...] "Wigmore Criteria" [...] are seen as a general framework, not a [...] "carved in stone" [...] approach. The [...] "Wigmore Criteria" [...] are generally used to determine if privilege covers communications that do not fall under the classic privileged communications such as solicitor-client privilege or <b>spousal</b> <b>privilege.</b>|$|E
